of impanate \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/impanate\">impanate</a>; <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of pabulum \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/pabulum\">pabulum</a>; <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of panatela \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/panatela\">panatela</a>; <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of panic \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/panic\">panic</a>（n.2）“一种草”； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of pannier \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/pannier\">pannier</a>; <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of panocha \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/panocha\">panocha</a>; <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of pantry \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/pantry\">pantry</a>; <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of pastern \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/pastern\">pastern</a>; <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of pastor \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/pastor\">pastor</a>; <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of pasture \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/pasture\">pasture</a>; <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of pester \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/pester\">pester</a>; <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of repast \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/repast\">repast</a>; <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of satrap \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/satrap\">satrap</a>。</p><p>它是以下词汇的假定来源/其存在的证据由以下提供：希腊语 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">pateisthai</i> “喂养”； 拉丁语 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">pabulum</i> “食物，饲料”， <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">panis</i> “面包”， <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">pasci</i> “喂养”， <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">pascare</i> “放牧，喂养